						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Matsyapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 9: 994 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is an inscription of Rājarāja I and it records a gift of a silver plate and a bronze stand to God Mahādēva in the temple at Tiruchchelūr by Sembiyaṉ Mahādēviyār, the mother of Uttama-chōḷa for the merit of her son.</p>						

